bitcoin-api-cpp
------------------------------------------
This is a C++ wrapper library for JSON-RPC communication with the Bitcoin
daemon. It allows developers to communicate with the Bitcoin daemon without the
need to pack and unpack JSON-RPC messages and thus simplifies the interaction
with it.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libbitcoinapi-devel-0.3.1-1bl1
  libbitcoinapi0-0.3.1-1bl1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libjsoncpp19-1.8.4-1
  libjsonrpccpp1-1.3.0-1bl1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/hkalodner/bitcoin-api-cpp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/hkalodner/bitcoin-api-cpp/archive/v0.3.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bitcoin-api-cpp-0.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bitcoin-api-cpp-0.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bitcoin-api-cpp-0.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bitcoin-api-cpp-0.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbitcoinapi0-0.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbitcoinapi-devel-0.3.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bitcoin-api-cpp)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bitcoin-api-cpp.README
  /usr/share/doc/bitcoin-api-cpp/README.md

(libbitcoinapi0)
  /usr/bin/cygbitcoinapi-0.dll

(libbitcoinapi-devel)
  /usr/include/bitcoinapi/bitcoinapi.h
  /usr/include/bitcoinapi/exception.h
  /usr/include/bitcoinapi/types.h
  /usr/lib/libbitcoinapi.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/bitcoin-api-cpp.pc

